<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_View::render() currently allows script names that include parent directory notation -- which could lead to a potential local filesystem inclusion exploit if provided unfiltered user input. As view scripts should only ever match <em>beneath</em> the registered view script directories, render() (or _script()) should filter for this sort of input and raise an exception when such input is detected.</p>

    </div>
</div>

